The paper focuses on developing a new neural network model for color image tasks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the compatibility of the proposed model with various deep learning techniques, indicating a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper proposes a new approach to representing color images using quaternion matrices, which could be considered a novel application of algebraic structures in computer science (cs.AI). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed model's performance in image denoising, which is a sub-topic of multimedia (cs.MM).
